The National Transport and Safety Authority has suspended 11 saccos for failing to operate a minimum of 30 serviceable motor vehicles. In a statement on Friday, NTSA director general Francis Meja asked Kenyans not to board vehicles owned by the Saccos. Among the Saccos suspended is  Teachers Transporters that operates through Khoja- Flyover-Engineer- Njabini- North Kinagop and back. They also ply the Khoja- Thika Road- Ngumba-Thome and Nairobi- Kiambaa-Naivasha-Nakuru to Nyahururu. Kitengela Minibus operating from Railways to Machakos was also suspended. Others include Smoke City, Seven City Sacco, Single Line Services, Gesarate Trade Links, Sunbird Services, Kazana Travellers, Snowball Sacco, Angel Kings and Kijabe Line Sacco. Their suspension took effect from October 17, NTSA said. Meja said traffic department officers will impound any vehicle belonging to the suspended Saccos found operating. On October 1, the authority suspended nine matatu Saccos for failing to comply with the provisions of the laws. Edited by R.Wamochie